---
title: Smoky Ratatouille (v) with Goat's Cheese and Garlic Bread
description: Smoked paprika is most definitely one of our favourite spices. Regular paprika is made by drying peppers in the sun then grinding them to a powder. For the smoked variety, the peppers are dried in smoke sheds using wood such as oak to impart a distinctive flavour. It’s a great store cupboard essential and adds a whole new dimension to your cooking. For this recipe, we balanced it against fresh, mild goat’s cheese.
